2743.text:
==================================
  README
==================================
Running this job will create tables in your redshift cluster!
* matillion_stg_airports
* matillion_us_state_lookup
* matillion_dim_airports

Internet access on the AMI instance is required to load from S3.

2744.text: Ask a colleague to join the action by sending them the URL above

2745.text:
Make some changes! 
Don't worry about breaking anything, because all actions can be undone via a right-click. 
The undo history is stored on the server, so even if you leave and come back later you can still undo.

2746.text: When all tables are loaded, run the transformation

2773.text:
Add 'Components' from the Components Palette. 

Connect them together to form a flow of data from source to target.

2774.text: You are viewing the "Default" version of your new project. You can save all the jobs within it in their current state by making a 'Version'. That way, you can continue to work on the default version knowing that you can always open and run a previous previous version. Editing a version requires unlocking, so you can't accidentally make changes (but they are still possible!)
